Ye concepts kyu use hote hain?

Taints, Tolerations aur Affinity se hum control karte hain:-->
    Kaunsa pod kis node par chale
    Kis node par na chale

1. Taints kya hoti hai?
   Taint node par lagti hai. Taint node par lagayi jaati hai taaki normal pods us node par schedule na ho sake.
Command:
  kubectl taint nodes worker1 env=prod:NoSchedule

Meaning:
worker1 node par taint lag gaya
Ab normal pod us node par run nahi karega

2. Tolerations kya hoti hai?
👉 Toleration pod me lagti hai. Mujhe tainted node par run karne do.

YAML:
     tolerations:
    - key: "env"
      operator: "Equal"
      value: "prod"
      effect: "NoSchedule"
Ab ye pod:
env=prod
taint wale node par run kar sakta hai.

3. Node Affinity kya hoti hai?
   Pod ko specific node par hi run karo.
   Ye node labels ke basis par kaam karta hai.

Node par label:
kubectl label node worker1 disk=ssd
YAML:
    affinity:
      nodeAffinity:
        requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
          nodeSelectorTerms:
          - matchExpressions:
            - key: disk
              operator: In
              values:
              - ssd

Ab pod sirf:
disk=ssd
wale node par hi chalega.


Difference :---->
Feature        	Kaam
Taint	          Node se pod ko door rakhta hai
Toleration    	Pod ko tainted node par allow karta hai
Affinity      	Pod ko specific node ki taraf attract karta hai

Short Answer:===>
Taints aur tolerations Kubernetes scheduling control ke liye use hote hain.
Taint node par lagta hai jo pods ko block karta hai, aur toleration pod me lagta hai jo us node par run karne ki permission deta hai.
Node affinity ka use specific labeled nodes par pods schedule karne ke liye hota hai.

OR

Taints node par lagti hain jo pods ko restrict karti hain.
Tolerations pod me lagti hain jo tainted node par pod ko run karne ki permission deti hain.
Node affinity ka use pods ko specific labeled nodes par schedule karne ke liye hota hai.


Real Production Use Case :===>
✅ Taints
    Dedicated DB nodes
    GPU nodes
✅ Tolerations
    Sirf database pods ko DB node par allow karna
✅ Node Affinity
    SSD nodes par high-performance app chalana


#####################################################################################################################
                                  Pod Affinity vs Pod Anti-Affinity
######################################################################################################################
Pod Affinity kya hoti hai?
Is pod ko dusre specific pod ke paas run karo

Use case:==>
App pod aur Redis pod same node par
Fast communication

Example

Suppose:
Backend pod already running
New pod ko backend ke same node par run karna hai

YAML:
affinity:
  podAffinity:
    requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
    - labelSelector:
        matchExpressions:
        - key: app
          operator: In
          values:
          - backend
      topologyKey: kubernetes.io/hostname


Result:
👉 New pod: backend pod ke same node parrun karega.

Pod Anti-Affinity kya hoti hai?
Anti-affinity ka matlab:  “Pods ko alag-alag nodes par run karo”

Use case:
High availability
Agar ek node down ho jaye to dusra pod chalta rahe

YAML:
affinity:
  podAntiAffinity:
    requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
    - labelSelector:
        matchExpressions:
        - key: app
          operator: In
          values:
          - nginx
      topologyKey: kubernetes.io/hostname

Result
👉 Nginx replicas: alag-alag nodes par run hongi.
